# Code Review: `isValidURL()`

## Issues Found

### 1. **Overly Permissive Pattern** (High Priority)
**Problem:** The regex `[^\s]+` matches any non-whitespace character, allowing invalid URLs.

```javascript
// These would incorrectly pass:
isValidURL('http://example.com<script>alert("xss")</script>')
isValidURL('http://example.com\n')
isValidURL('http://[invalid]')
```

**Fix:** Use a more restrictive pattern or built-in validation:
```javascript
function isValidURL(str) {
  try {
    new URL(str);
    return /^https?:\/\//.test(str);
  } catch {
    return false;
  }
}
```

---

### 2. **No Input Validation** (Medium Priority)
**Problem:** No null/undefined/type checks before testing.

```javascript
isValidURL(null)        // Returns false (acceptable but implicit)
isValidURL(undefined)   // Returns false
isValidURL(123)         // Returns false (should reject explicitly)
```

**Fix:**
```javascript
function isValidURL(str) {
  if (typeof str !== 'string' || str.length === 0) {
    return false;
  }
  try {
    new URL(str);
    return /^https?:\/\//.test(str);
  } catch {
    return false;
  }
}
```

---

### 3. **Regex Recompilation** (Low Priority - Performance)
**Problem:** Pattern is recompiled on every function call.

**Fix:**
```javascript
const URL_PATTERN = /^https?:\/\//;

function isValidURL(str) {
  if (typeof str !== 'string' || str.length === 0) {
    return false;
  }
  try {
    new URL(str);
    return URL_PATTERN.test(str);
  } catch {
    return false;
  }
}
```

---

### 4. **Missing Protocol Validation** (Medium Priority)
**Problem:** Doesn't validate that the protocol is actually http/https.

```javascript
isValidURL('ftp://example.com')  // Returns false ✓ (good)
isValidURL('http://example.com') // Returns true ✓
```
This one is actually okay, but worth documenting.

---

## Improved Version

```javascript
const URL_PATTERN = /^https?:\/\//;

function isValidURL(str) {
  // Type and basic validation
  if (typeof str !== 'string' || str.trim().length === 0) {
    return false;
  }

  try {
    // Use native URL constructor for robust parsing
    const url = new URL(str);
    // Ensure protocol is http or https
    return URL_PATTERN.test(url.href);
  } catch {
    return false;
  }
}

// Test cases
console.log(isValidURL('https://example.com'));           // true
console.log(isValidURL('http://example.com/path?q=1'));   // true
console.log(isValidURL('ftp://example.com'));             // false
console.log(isValidURL('not a url'));                     // false
